Marius,

Given that the code is croaking presumably at the last line of this method in 
the BuildManager.java:

      public void run() throws Exception {
        IProject[] builders = currentBuilder.build(trigger, args, monitor);
        if (builders == null)
          builders = new IProject[0];
        currentBuilder.setInterestingProjects((IProject[]) builders.clone());
      }
And given that builders can't possibly be null, it must be the currentBuilder 
that's null.  But since the first line didn't get the null pointer exception, 
this looks like some type of timing problem.  I certainly can't reproduce 
this problem with a simpler example, so it's not something fundamentally wrong 
in the JETBuilder, which hasn't changed in months.  

I think either the platform folks need to look at this or you need to consider 
helping them since you have the rather hefty environment that reproduces the 
problem.
